HONG KONG
Hong Kong Harbor is one of the busiest in all Asia. It bustles with
ferres... carving half a million passengers a day...and
freighters and endless junks and sampans. At Aberdeen, you
will find a whole village of people who live all their lives on boats
Across the harbor in Kowloon, shops and stalls bulge with
merchandise as shoppers bargain noisily. The Furama
Inter • Continental is centrally located and provides a wide range
of amenities. Pan Am serves Hong Kong every day on its
Round-The-World flights, from New York via Tokyo
and nonstop from San Francisco
PAN AM
